#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:2
msgid "Rust_EMIT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:7
msgid "Experimental. Gated by ``CMAKE_EXPERIMENTAL_RUST``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:9
msgid ""
"This property controls the type of output generated by the Rust compiler. "
"Can be one of several values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:12
msgid "``link``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:13
msgid ""
"This is the default if the property is not set. The crate will be compiled "
"into an `rlib` file, e.g.: ``libfile.rs.rlib``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:17
msgid ""
"CMake will automatically prefix the generated ``rlib`` file with ``lib`` as "
"the Rust compiler always requires such a prefix for external crates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:21
msgid "``obj``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:22
msgid "Generate a native object file, e.g.: ``file.rs.o``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:24
msgid "``asm``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:25
msgid "Generate an assembly file, e.g.: ``file.rs.s``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:28
msgid ""
"The ``obj`` and ``asm`` output types are known to have the following "
"limitations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:31
msgid ""
"When enabled, the Rust compiler disables multiple codegen units and ThinLTO. "
"Depending on the situation, this can affect the generated code, "
"optimizations. It also reduce the internal parallelism inside and the "
"compiler and can reduce the effectiveness of incremental rebuilds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:35
msgid ""
"The generated ``obj`` files cannot be used as external crates, so other Rust "
"code can only use C-style API from them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_sf/Rust_EMIT.rst:37
msgid ""
"The generated ``obj`` files cannot be linked as-is with native linkers, "
"additional crates from the Rust toolchain needs to linked too. The actual "
"crates to link depend on the code and compiler options."
msgstr ""
